.TH "WEBGL2RENDERINGCONTEXT.COMPRESSEDTEXIMAGE3D" "3JS" "August 27, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
WebGL2RenderingContext.compressedTexImage3D \- WebGL2RenderingContext:
compressedTexImage3D() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This feature is available in Web Workers.
.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]compressedTexImage3D()\f[B]\f[R] method of the
\f[CR]WebGL2RenderingContext\f[R] interface of the WebGL API specifies a
three\-dimensional texture image in a compressed format.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
compressedTexImage3D(target, level, internalformat, width, height, depth, border, imageSize, offset)

compressedTexImage3D(target, level, internalformat, width, height, depth, border, srcData)
compressedTexImage3D(target, level, internalformat, width, height, depth, border, srcData, srcOffset)
compressedTexImage3D(target, level, internalformat, width, height, depth, border, srcData, srcOffset, srcLengthOverride)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]target\f[R]
A \f[CR]GLenum\f[R] specifying the binding point (target) of the active
compressed texture.
Possible values:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]gl.TEXTURE_3D\f[R]: A three\-dimensional texture.
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]gl.TEXTURE_2D_ARRAY\f[R]: A two\-dimensional array texture.
.RE
.TP
\f[B]level\f[R]
A \f[CR]GLint\f[R] specifying the level of detail.
Level 0 is the base image level and level \f[I]n\f[R] is the n\-th
mipmap reduction level.
.TP
\f[B]internalformat\f[R]
A \f[CR]GLenum\f[R] specifying the compressed image format.
For a list of possible values, see
\f[CR]WebGLRenderingContext.compressedTexImage2D()\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]width\f[R]
A \f[CR]GLsizei\f[R] specifying the width of the texture in texels.
.TP
\f[B]height\f[R]
A \f[CR]GLsizei\f[R] specifying the height of the texture in texels.
.TP
\f[B]depth\f[R]
A \f[CR]GLsizei\f[R] specifying the depth of the texture/the number of
textures in a \f[CR]TEXTURE_2D_ARRAY\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]border\f[R]
A \f[CR]GLint\f[R] specifying the width of the border.
Must be 0.
.PP
The texture source can be provided in one of two ways: from an
\f[CR]ArrayBuffer\f[R] (possibly shared) using \f[CR]srcData\f[R],
\f[CR]srcOffset\f[R], and \f[CR]srcLengthOverride\f[R]; or from
\f[CR]gl.PIXEL_UNPACK_BUFFER\f[R] using \f[CR]imageSize\f[R] and
\f[CR]offset\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]srcData\f[R]
A \f[CR]TypedArray\f[R] or \f[CR]DataView\f[R] containing the compressed
texture data.
.TP
\f[B]srcOffset\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
An integer specifying the index of \f[CR]srcData\f[R] to start reading
from.
Defaults to \f[CR]0\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]srcLengthOverride\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
An integer specifying the number of elements in \f[CR]srcData\f[R] to
read.
Defaults to \f[CR]srcData.length \- srcOffset\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]imageSize\f[R]
A \f[CR]GLsizei\f[R] specifying the size of the image data in bytes.
.TP
\f[B]offset\f[R]
A \f[CR]GLintptr\f[R] specifying the starting address in the buffer
bound to \f[CR]gl.PIXEL_UNPACK_BUFFER\f[R].
.SS Return value
None (\f[CR]undefined\f[R]).
